POWER BI

 1.
1. Create Map:
   - Import dataset into Power BI.
   - Use the Map visual, dragging Latitude and Longitude to the respective wells.
   - Add Country Name to the Location well.
2. Format Map:
   - Customize map style, bubble size, and data colors.


 2.
1. Create Bar Graph:
   - Drag Year to Axis and GDP to Values.
   - Filter for Belgium.
2. Format Graph:
   - Add title: *“GDP of Belgium (2006 – 2026)”*.
   - Adjust colors and axes.


 3. 
1. Create Pie Chart:
   - Drag Country Name to Legend and GDP to Values.
   - Filter for Year = 2010 and select countries.
2. Format Chart:
   - Show percentages and customize colors.


 4. 
1. Create Chart:
   - Drag Country Name to Axis and GDP to Values.
   - Filter for Bhutan and Costa Rica.
2. Format Chart:
   - Add title: *“GDP Comparison: Bhutan vs. Costa Rica”*.


 5.
1. Create Scatter Plot:
   - Drag Year to X-Axis, GDP to Y-Axis, and Country Name to Details.
   - Filter data for 2004–2006.
2. Format Plot:
   - Add title and customize data points.
